Habitat. The specimens were collected using Malaise traps placed at the ground level in the following areas: a sugar cane plantation (
Sacharum officinarum
); a tropical humid forest reserve in the Colombian Amazon; Departament of Caquetá , Parque Nacional Natural La Paya with savanna vegetation; floodplain forests of the Orinoco region at Parque Nacional Natural La Macarena; the dry tropical forest of the Andean region in the Santuario de Fauna y Flora Iguaque and the Caribbean region at Santuario de Fauna y Flora Los Colorados.
